songs.lyrics:
It's a good day, It's a good day

Well, it's a good day, for singing a song
And it's a good day, for moving along
Yes it's a good day, how could anything go wrong
It's a good day from morning till night

And it's a good day, for shining your shoes
And it's a good day, for losing the blues
Everything to gain, and nothing to lose
It's a good day from morning till night

I said to the sun, Good morning sun
Rise and shine today
You know you've gotta get moving
If you're gonna get showing and you
Got the right of way

Cause it's a good day, It's a good day

Yes, it's a good day, for starting anew
And it's a good day, for thinking of you
It's a good day and there's so much to do
It's a good day from morning till night

And it's a good day for being yourself
Yes, it's a good day for losing yourself
It's a good day, leave your worries on the shelf
It's a good day, from morning till night

I said to the sun, Good morning sun
Rise and shine today
You know you've gotta get moving
If you've gotta get showing and you
Got the right of way

Cause it's a good day for paying your bills
And it's a good day, for curing your ills
So take a deep breath, and throw away the pills
Cause it's a good day, from morning till night
It's a good day, from morning till night
It's a good day, from morning till night

songs.embed_content: Read “Loving You” by Cyrille Aimée on Genius
songs.title: Loving You

album.full_title: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure by Cyrille Aimée
album.name: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure

songs.lyrics:
[Verse]
Loving you is not a choice
It's who I am
Loving you is not a choice
Not much reason to rejoice
But it gives me purpose
Gives me voice
To say to the world
This is why I live
You are why I live

[Chorus]
Loving you is why I do the things I do
Loving you is not in my control
But loving you, I have a goal
For what's left on my life
I will live
And I would die
For you

[Instrumental Break]

[Chorus]
Loving you is why I do the things I do
Loving you is not in my control
But loving you, I have a goal
For what's left on my life
I will live
And I would die
I will live
And I would die
For you

songs.embed_content: Read “Being Alive” by Cyrille Aimée on Genius
songs.title: Being Alive

album.full_title: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure by Cyrille Aimée
album.name: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Someone to hold you too close
Someone to hurt you too deep
Someone to sit in your chair
To ruin your sleep
Someone to need you too much
Someone to know you too well
Someone to pull you up short
And put you through hell

[Verse 2]
Someone you have to let in
Someone who's feelings you spare
Someone who, like it or not
Will want you to share, a little, a lot
Someone to crowd you with love
Someone to force you to care
Someone to make you come through
Who'll always be there as frightened as you
Of being alive, being alive, being alive
Being alive

[Verse 3]
Somebody, need me too much
Somebody, know me too well
Somebody, pull me up short
And put me through hell
And give me support
For being alive
Make me alive
Make me alive
Make me confused

[Interlude]
Mock me with praise
Let me be used
Vary my days
But alone is alone, not alive

[Verse 4]
Somebody, crowd me with love
Somebody, force me to care
Somebody, let me come through
I'll always be there
As frightened as you
To help us survive
Being alive
Being alive
Being alive
Being alive (Woo)
Being alive (Ooh)
Being alive (Ooh)
Being alive

[Verse 5]
Somebody, hold me too close (Being alive)
Somebody, hurt me too deep (Being alive)
Somebody, sit in my chair (Being alive)
Somebody, crowd me with love (Being alive)
Somebody, need me (Being alive)
Somebody, know me (Being alive)
Somebody, let me come through (Being alive)
Somebody, sit in my chair (Being alive)
And force me to care
And make me aware (Being alive)
And ruin my sleep

[Scatting Interlude]

[Outro]
Being alive
Being alive
Being alive

annotatable.link_title: Marry Me a Little by Cyrille Aimée
annotatable.title: Marry Me a Little

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Marry me a little
Love me just enough
Cry but not too often
Play but not too rough
Keep a tender distance
So we'll both be free
That’s the way it ought to be
I'm ready
Marry me a little
Do it with a will
Make a few demands
I'm able to fulfill
Want me more than others
Not exclusively
That’s the way it ought to be
I'm ready
I'm ready now

[Verse 2]
You can be my best friend
I can be your right arm
We'll go through a fight or two
No harm, no harm
We'll look not too deep
We'll go not too far
We won't have to give up a thing
We'll stay who we are
Right?
Okay, then
I’m ready
I’m ready now

[Verse 3]
Marry me a little
Love me just enough
Warm and sweet and easy
Just the simple stuff
Keep a tender distance
So we'll both be free
That’s the way it ought to be
I'm ready
Marry me a little
Body, heart, and soul
Passionate as hell
But always in control
Want me first and foremost
Keep me company
That's the way it ought to be
I'm ready
I’m ready now

[Verse 4]
Oh, how gently we'll talk
Oh, how softly we'll tread
All the strings
The ugly things
We'll keep unsaid
We'll build a cocoon
Of love and respect
You'll promise whatever you like
I'll never collect
Right?

[Outro]
Okay, then
I'm ready
I'm ready now
Someone
I'm ready

songs.embed_content: Read “Move On” by Cyrille Aimée on Genius
songs.title: Move On

album.full_title: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure by Cyrille Aimée
album.name: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I've nothing to say
Well nothing that's not been said
I do not know where to go
I want to make things that count, things that will be new
What am I to do?

[Verse 2]
I want to move on
I want to explore the light
I want to know how to get through
Through to something new
Move on
Move on

[Verse 3]
Stop worrying where you're going
Move on
If you can know where you're going
You've gone
Just keep moving on

[Verse 4]
Look at what you want
Now at where you are
Not at what you'll be
Look at all the things you've done for me
Opened up my eyes
Taught me how to see
Notice every tree
Understand the light
Concentrate on now
Move on
Move on

[Verse 3]
Stop worrying if your vision is new
Let others make that decision
They usually do
You keep moving on

[Verse 4]
Something in the light
Something in the sky
Up behind the trees
Flower in your hat
And your smile
And the color of your hair
And the way you catch the light
And the care
And the feeling
And the life
Moving on

[Outro]
Anything you do
Let it come from you
Let it come from you
Then it will be new
Give us more to see

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Un dernier baiser d'adieu
Un baiser sans retour
Jamais on ne se reverra
Prends moi dans tes bras mon tendre amour

[Verse 2]
Un baiser du bout des yeux
Me rappelle au passé
Au pays des souvenirs
Nos deux coeurs chavirent, nos corps enlacés

[Verse 3]
Ce rêve sans pariel
Mais brisé par l'éveil
Entre dans la danse
Plus aucune chance
D'être ou d'espérer
N'y pensons plus, n'y pensons plus

[Verse 4]
Un dernier baiser précieux
Sans soupirs ni pleurs
Faut-il que la passion meurt?
Déja est t'elle éteinte?
Le derniere étreinte
Un baiser d'adieu

songs.embed_content: Read “I Remember” by Cyrille Aimée on Genius
songs.title: I Remember

album.full_title: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure by Cyrille Aimée
album.name: Move On: A Sondheim Adventure

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I remember sky
It was blue as ink
Or at least I think
I remember sky
I remember snow
Soft as feathers
Sharp as thumbtacks
Coming down like lint
And it made you squint
When the wind would blow

[Verse 2]
And ice like vinyl
On the streets
Cold as silver
White as sheets
Rain like strings
And changing things
Like leaves
I remember leaves
Green as spearmint
Crisp as paper
I remember trees
Bare as coat racks
Spread like broken umbrellas
And parks and bridges
Ponds and zoos
Ruddy faces
Muddy shoes
Light and noise and
Bees and boys
And days

[Verse 3]
I remember days
Or at least I try
But as years go by
They're a sort of haze
And the bluest ink
Isn’t really sky
And at times I think
I would gladly die
For a day of sky
